findings.title: Potential unauthorized script upgrade
findings.description: N/A

findings.title: Unprotected approve function
findings.description: The approve function is unprotected, allowing unauthorized access and potential token theft.

findings.title: Unprotected transfer function
findings.description: The 'transfer' function is unprotected and can be exploited by malicious users.

findings.title: Unprotected transferFrom function
findings.description: The transferFrom function is not protected, allowing unauthorized access and potential token theft.

findings.title: Unprotected increaseAllowance function
findings.description: The increaseAllowance function does not have any access control or validation checks, allowing unauthorized users to increase the allowance of an arbitrary user.

findings.title: Unprotected decreaseAllowance function
findings.description: The decreaseAllowance function is unprotected and can be exploited by an attacker.

findings.title: Unprotected _transfer function
findings.description: The _transfer function is unprotected and can be exploited by malicious actors.

findings.title: Unprotected _mint function
findings.description: The _mint function is unprotected and can be exploited by an attacker to mint tokens without authorization.

findings.title: Unprotected _burn function
findings.description: The _burn function is unprotected and can be exploited by an attacker.

findings.title: Unprotected _approve function
findings.description: The _approve function is unprotected and can be exploited to approve arbitrary amounts.

findings.title: Unprotected permit function
findings.description: The permit function does not have sufficient access control, allowing unauthorized users to call it.

findings.title: Unprotected mint function
findings.description: The mint function is unprotected, allowing anyone to mint tokens without restriction.

findings.title: Unprotected burn function
findings.description: The _burn function is internal and does not have any access modifiers, making it vulnerable to unauthorized access.

findings.title: Unprotected swap function
findings.description: The private functions 'swapAndSendToFee', 'swapAndLiquify', 'swapTokensForEth', 'swapTokensForCake' and 'swapAndSendDividends' are unprotected, allowing unauthorized access.

findings.title: Unprotected skim function
findings.description: The skim function is unprotected, allowing unauthorized access and potential manipulation of sensitive data.

findings.title: Unprotected sync function
findings.description: The process function is declared as public and does not have any access modifiers, making it vulnerable to unauthorized access.

findings.title: Unprotected initialize function
findings.description: The initialize function is unprotected and can be called by anyone, potentially leading to unintended behavior or security risks.

findings.title: Reentrancy risk in transfer and other functions
findings.description: The contract contains reentrancy risks in its transfer function and possibly other functions, allowing an attacker to drain the contract's funds.

findings.title: Lack of input validation in various functions
findings.description: The functions get, getIndexOfKey, getKeyAtIndex, size, set, remove, dividendOf, withdrawDividend, withdrawableDividendOf, withdrawnDividendOf, and accumulativeDividendOf do not perform input validation.
findings.function: get, getIndexOfKey, getKeyAtIndex, size, set, remove, dividendOf, withdrawDividend, withdrawableDividendOf, withdrawnDividendOf, accumulativeDividendOf
